The paper introduces a novel semi-supervised learning technique for the Semantic Image Interpretation (SII) task, which involves using relational background knowledge to benefit from unlabeled data. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computation and Language (cs.CL), and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). However, given the focus on image interpretation and the use of background knowledge, cs.AI and cs.CV are the most likely categories, followed by cs.LG, cs.CL, and cs.CR.
